 Plan: T1.4 — Monetización con Stripe

 Contexto

 Agregar planes de pago por tiers al Action Extractor. El usuario ya tiene cuenta Stripe pero
 sin productos configurados. Se usará Stripe Checkout (redirect) como flujo de pago.

 Planes:

 ┌──────────┬─────────┬───────────────────┐
 │   Plan   │ Precio  │ Extracciones/hora │
 ├──────────┼─────────┼───────────────────┤
 │ Free     │ $0      │ 12 (default env)  │
 ├──────────┼─────────┼───────────────────┤
 │ Pro      │ $15/mes │ 60                │
 ├──────────┼─────────┼───────────────────┤
 │ Business │ $49/mes │ 200               │
 └──────────┴─────────┴───────────────────┘

 Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, PostgreSQL (pg pool)
 Nuevo paquete: stripe npm package

 ---
 Paso 0 — Setup previo en Stripe Dashboard (usuario hace esto manualmente)

 1. Crear producto "Pro" → precio recurrente $15/mes → copiar Price ID
 2. Crear producto "Business" → precio recurrente $49/mes → copiar Price ID
 3. Agregar vars en docker-stack/docker-compose.yaml (servicio action-extractor):
 STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
 STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
 STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY=price_...
 STRIPE_PRICE_BUSINESS_MONTHLY=price_...
 4. Para webhooks en dev: stripe listen --forward-to
 https://roi.welltechnologies.net/api/stripe/webhook

 ---
 Paso 1 — Instalar Stripe SDK

 docker compose exec action-extractor npm install stripe

 ---
 Paso 2 — DB (lib/db.ts)

 DB_INIT_SIGNATURE → '2026-02-28-stripe-v1'

 Nuevas ALTERs y tablas en INIT_SQL:
 -- Agregar stripe_customer_id a users
 ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS stripe_customer_id TEXT;
 CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_users_stripe_customer_id
   ON users(stripe_customer_id) WHERE stripe_customer_id IS NOT NULL;

 -- Tabla de planes por usuario
 CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS user_plans (
   id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
   plan TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'free',           -- 'free' | 'pro' | 'business'
   extractions_per_hour INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 12,
   stripe_subscription_id TEXT,
   stripe_price_id TEXT,
   status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active',       -- 'active' | 'canceled' | 'past_due'
   current_period_start TIMESTAMPTZ,
   current_period_end TIMESTAMPTZ,
   canceled_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
   updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
 );
 CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_user_plans_user_active
   ON user_plans(user_id) WHERE status = 'active';
 CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_user_plans_stripe_sub
   ON user_plans(stripe_subscription_id) WHERE stripe_subscription_id IS NOT NULL;

 -- Log de eventos Stripe (idempotencia)
 CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS stripe_events (
   id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
   event_type TEXT NOT NULL,
   user_id TEXT REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
   processed BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
   raw_json TEXT NOT NULL,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
 );
 CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_stripe_events_type ON stripe_events(event_type);

 Nuevas funciones DB (lib/db.ts):
 - getUserActivePlan(userId) → SELECT FROM user_plans WHERE user_id=$1 AND status='active' LIMIT 1
 - getUserPlanRateLimit(userId) → async: llama getUserActivePlan, retorna extractions_per_hour o
 resolveExtractionRateLimitPerHour() si no hay plan
 - upsertUserActivePlan(input: { userId, plan, extractionsPerHour, subscriptionId, priceId,
 periodStart, periodEnd }) → INSERT ... ON CONFLICT(user_id) WHERE status='active' DO UPDATE
 - deactivateUserPlan(userId, subscriptionId) → UPDATE user_plans SET status='canceled',
 canceled_at=NOW()
 - setUserStripeCustomerId(userId, stripeCustomerId) → UPDATE users SET stripe_customer_id=$2
 - getUserByStripeCustomerId(stripeCustomerId) → SELECT FROM users WHERE stripe_customer_id=$1
