 POST /api/stripe/checkout/route.ts

 1. Auth requerida
 2. Body: { planId: 'pro' | 'business' }
 3. Obtener priceId de PLAN_PRICE_IDS[planId]
 4. Buscar si user tiene stripe_customer_id → usar como customer, si no usar customer_email
 5. stripe.checkout.sessions.create({ mode:'subscription', line_items, success_url, cancel_url,
 metadata: { userId } })
 6. Retornar { url: session.url }

 POST /api/stripe/portal/route.ts

 1. Auth requerida
 2. Requiere que user tenga stripe_customer_id
 3. stripe.billingPortal.sessions.create({ customer, return_url })
 4. Retornar { url }

 POST /api/stripe/webhook/route.ts

 - NO auth — valida con firma Stripe
 - export const runtime = 'nodejs'
 - Leer body como texto: const rawBody = await req.text()
 - stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(rawBody, sig, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET)
 - Eventos:
   - checkout.session.completed:
       - Obtener subscription via stripe.subscriptions.retrieve(session.subscription)
     - setUserStripeCustomerId(userId, session.customer)
     - upsertUserActivePlan({ userId, plan, extractionsPerHour, subscriptionId, priceId, ... })
   - customer.subscription.updated:
       - Buscar userId via getUserByStripeCustomerId(event.data.object.customer)
     - Actualizar estado del plan
   - customer.subscription.deleted:
       - deactivateUserPlan(userId, subscriptionId)
 - Log idempotente con logStripeEvent

 GET /api/account/plan/route.ts

 1. Auth requerida
 2. getUserActivePlan(userId) → si null, retornar plan free
 3. Retorna: { plan, extractionsPerHour, status, currentPeriodEnd, hasStripeCustomer }

